a-size-base: Great treats for the little kitties!
a-size-base 2: Reviewed in the United States on July 29, 2023
a-size-base 3: Our 12 week old kitten has been eating these for a few weeks now and as his Mom, I feel really good about the ingredients and good amounts of protein, fat, and moisture in them. He's not food motivated at all and has been super accepting of his diet that includes free feeding good quality kibble with canned offered instead a few days a week. He definitely loves and wants that canned food but even then, never really eats with gusto. I say all this to explain that he just doesn't get all that excited over any food, but he does enjoy these treats.They are rather large, at least 5x the size of a single piece of kitten kibble, but no problem, because breaking these treats up is easy and makes treat time last a little longer.I also worried that these treats would arrive all smashed and broken as some reviewers have experienced, but that wasn't the case here. Lots of soft little hearts that I can break up myself.I feel good that I'm offering a healthy, low calorie treat, and that that my silly, wild, non-food-motivated little guy likes them enough to pause his crazy play time for one of these.
